column5: Does anyone know the closest launch to Pontypool? I want to lake test a boat. Tomorrow or Saturday.

Probably on Scugog in Caesarea or Rice Lake at Bewdley or Gores Landing?  BTW, have you ever seen the movie Pontypool?   For some reason I watched that movie and about a year later I drove through Pontypool then realizing it's a real town.
View lake on scugog. Lived in pontypool for years. In cavan now.  S.
If you need directions, pm me.  S.
Port Darlington is aboutb20 minutes away
The launch in newcastle is another option for concrete ramp with a dock. Also free. As long as the conditions allow, its a good spot for a test run.  S.
And don't forget to throw a few rods on the boat for test run !!!!! An hour testing the boat and 2 hours fishing !!!
You could go to Ommemee  quick. Launch in town. I would go north and launch at RiverView bridge.
